<Author>jesika10000
<Content>Great choice in Paris!!! My husband and I just returned from a 5 night stay in Paris. We enjoyed welcoming 2009 from the Champs Elysees and this hotel was the perfect choice. We spent hours researching hotels, looking for a great location, nice room, etc at a decent price (as our US exchange rate doesn't help much). This hotel met our needs. The rooms and bathrooms were nice, clean, average size (nothing fancy - but we really only slept there and spent our days wandering around Paris). The location was the best part. A very short walk to the Arc, The Champs, the Concord, great shopping, dining and more. If you need them, the metro and bus stops are on the Champs, a very quick and safe 5 min or less. walk away. There is also an EXCELLENT pharmacy/mini grocery store 2 doors down with cosmetics, toiletries, asprin, fresh breads, foods, cofffee, wines, bottled water and nice french food gifts like truffle mayo and other treats. The train station and bus stop to/from the airports is only 4 streets away. We were both very pleased with our stay here and highly recommend this hotel. The concierge and front desk are most helpful and will make suggestions and restaurant reservations for you. My only complaint is that I could hear some noise from the upstairs room above us, we were on the 4th fl, but I think the guests were unusually loud. The woman would wear heels in the room at niight and early morning and I could hear them on the wooden floors, they had a few loud fights and I think they moved furniture around for some strange reason. Of course not the fault of the hotel- just rude guests. Make sure when you book to look for special discounts (AAA rates, Internet specials etc). We had a really great rate AAA rate on a standard room -lower than what I see from other comments here. I also didn't add photos because I feel the photos posted are a true and current representation of the hotel. I didn't give this 5 stars only because I reserve that for situation I feel are truly unique, however there is nothing wrong with this hotel and I would return again. 
