<Author>TravelWithSuying
<Content>A Superb 5 Star Hotel The Radisson Hotel along the Champs Elysees is definitely a superb hotel without doubt! It's exactly the kind of hotel that we are all yearning for: 1) Soft sparkling clean bed2) All bedroom facilities maintained at top conditions it almost looked new3) A door partition between the bathroom and the bedroom so any business you make won't affect the fragrance of your bedroom4) Clean and dust free furnitures5) Air conditioning even in winter times so you do not have to open the windows and expose yourself to the dust and dry air.5) Bathroom is sparkling clean without any stains6) Bathroom comes with a speaker so you can listen to the tv news while you are bathing7) A good coffee maker8) Good selection of tv programs10) Prompt room service9) Fantastic concierge services10) Staffs who LISTENS to your request and satisfies them11) Situated along the glamourous shopping malls12) Situated near the historical icon Arc De Tromphe13) Situated near the train stationDuring my short 2 nights stopover in Paris, I had actually booked for another hotel near champs elysees on the internet and it had explicitly deceived me into believing that all their hotel rooms had air conditioning during winter times. Although i understand that it is usually the culture that hotels will not provide air conditioning during winter season, I needed air conditioning as I could not be exposed to winter air for a long period due to very dry skin conditions. Hence, I booked for the hotel believing their advert that they have air conditioning even in winter times. However, when i reached the hotel everything was a scam. 1) The hotel room was so small i had difficulty opening the wardrobe door.2) The bedsheets were filled with dust.3) One smack on the pillows will set the dust flying over your face! Horrible. 4) Air conditioning worked on a central control system, hence there was no way I could request for air conditioning for my room. 5) The safebox was spoilt. Needless to say, I made a complaint to the frontdesk. Only to see that they were rude and adamant about their services and the wrongly advertised information.Not wanting it to dampen my holiday mood, i went out of the hotel in search of a better hotel and that was where i stumbled up the concierge staff Radisson Hotel! Everything took a drastic change from here. The concierge was highly professional who spoke with grace, enthusiasm and politeness. Immediately they showed me to the room which is available for our consideration and offered to transfer our luggages from the nasty hotel to theirs! Their service was professional and efficient.Hence without further ado I went back to the hotel, spoke with the manager about my situation, waived the penalty payment of cancellation of hotel booking fees and dived straight into the cozy arms of Radisson!Don't despise this seemingly small hotel of Radisson, you will feel immediate elegance and professionalism of their hotel staffs right at their door step. Rest assured for a memorable holiday. A place not to be missed.Enjoy! Suying 
