<Content>Location, location, location. This is a wonderful Hotel within walking distance to most of the touristy sights. The Arc de Triomphe is literally 2-3 minutes walk away. The rooms are fairly small but beautifully furnished and spotlessly clean. The bathroom was gorgeous and suprisingly large with very good quality towels and toiletries. Although the hotel was almost full whilst we were there we didn't know it as it was so quiet and peaceful. Just off the lobby there is an outside terrace where they serve dinner/drinks, a real treat if you want to sit in the sun and relax after a days sightseeing. Just outside of the hotel heading right is a fantastic store, I think it is called the Drugstore . It has a fantastic deli-counter, toiletries, gifts, make-up, wine, newspapers, I could go on! We were given recommendations to eat in the evening in the St. Germain district and we were not disappointed. The area felt very safe and there was a huge choice of wonderful places to eat. Overall I was blown away with Paris, I never expected it to be quite so beautiful. For a large city it also felt suprisingly safe. We can't wait to visit again with the kids when they are older and I would definately stay at this hotel again. 
