<Author>NomadPrincess
<Content>Great Location and good hotel! My husband and I have recently returned from a long weekend at this hotel and were really pleased that we chose to go here. The hotel is conveniently located, just a couple of minutes walk from the Charles de Gaule Etoile Metro station and right next to the Arc de Triomphe and Champs Elysees.We decided to go for the 'Room with a View' package and got a good view of the Arc de Triomphe from our bedroom. The bedroom was larger than I expected it to be with a comfortable bed, plasma TV, mini bar, bathroom with bath and separate shower cubicle and very clean and tidy throughout. We also got a complimentary bottle of Champagne. It wasn't in the room on arrival but without prompting they brought it up to our room later that day and it was there for us to enjoy when we got back from our afternoon sight seeing. The Reception staff and bar staff were all friendly, helpful and cheerful. We had a full English breakfast included in our package. Unlike other hotels there is not a buffet but waiter service which will bring your choice to the table. Personally I preferred this as it was a more relaxing experience than battling for food with a crowd of people. There was plenty to eat. Choice of juice, choice of tea, coffee or hot chocolate (incidentally hot chocolate is to die for so give it a try!), big basket of pastries with jams. The cooked breakfast has sausage, egg any style, bacon, mushrooms and tomato and is cooked to order so hot and fresh. By the time you are finished you will be more than full enough to see through to lunchtime!The hotel itself is quite small so there are not any more amenities than necessary, so if you are looking for an all singing, all dancing type establishment then this isn't for you. However, if you like relaxed and peaceful surroundings with a boutique feel that is close to the Metro and has excellent accessability for all parts of Paris then this is a very good choice and you will enjoy your stay. 
