<Author>2007reviewer
<Content>totally overrated I picked this hotel, as i do most of the hotels i stay at via tripadvisor. unfortunately, i was completely unimpressed and think this is a VERY mediocre hotel, and WAY overpriced. All of my other experiences with tripadvisor have been much closer to the mark.I booked directly through the radisson website and for the price of $370 euros per night for a five night stay was supposed to receive the following: (1) arc de triomphe view, (2) no smoking room, (3) king bed in a deluxe room, and (4) champagne on arrival.Here are my major complaints:1. This hotel is priced very highly, i believe based on the fact thatthey advertise and promise an arc de triomphe view and have beautifulpictures on their website where it looks like you can eat on your balcony with the arc gloriously in view. in my opinion, this is very deceptive advertising. In fact, the hotelfaces into an office building across the street--that is the view yousee when you are in the room. The only arc view is if you go on the balcony (which is no more than two feet wide and four feet long and doesn't even have room to sit), stand and turn your head to look down the street. The pictures on the website, where there is a large table and people are enjoying a meal with the arc hugely impressive in the background is from the one suite in the hotel (it is not what you see from the deluxe room i booked!!!)2. the deluxe room we were given is much smaller than the majority ofpictures on the website. There was one small chair in the corner and sitting in it my knees touched the bed. Some of the website photos show rooms that were almost twice as large as ours. Not sure if we just got the one bad room in the bunch or if the website photos aren't representative. Based on my experience with this hotel, i would guess it was the later.3. in addition the bed is very uncomfortable--it is a thin mattress on a slat frame--there is no box spring, etc. Of the 7 hotels in italy and france we spent time at during this trip, this was by far the worst bed.4. I won't nitpick about other things, because the three above prettymuch left me cold. in addition, though, we were given a smoking room and only noticed after having spent 30 minutes unpacking--despite thefact that our confirmed reservation was for a non-smoking room and wenever received our champagne. As i have now gone back and re-read some of the reviews, both of these seem to be common occurrences at this hotel.this hotel is in a good area, but you know what, there are hundreds of well located paris hotels. after my bad experience the first night, i started calling to switch hotels, and for the same price (ora price within 20 or so euros), i found rooms at some of paris' best hotels--the crillon and the intercontinental (now the westin)--although the rooms at these hotels didn't include breakfast--still, the choice was totally clear. We ended up at the westin in a room about three times the size of our room at the radisson.i raised all of these concerns with the management and i'm not reallysure they cared. i would never stay at this hotel again and would warn you to read all the reviews carefully, because i think the cumulative score on tripadvisor is very misleading for this particular hotel. 
