<Content>It could have been so good. My wife and I booked this hotel for our honeymoon. We paid a bit extra for a superior room with a view (and a free bottle of champagne). Like the rest of Paris, it was quite expensive. I couldn't seem to find any cheap deals on the web, so just booked through the Radisson website. We stayed there at the start of June 07.Upon arrival we were told that the water on our floor wasn't working. Consequently, we had to stay in another hotel for our first night. The only place on offer (apparently, as Paris was so busy!) was the Concorde La Fayette. This gets an average rating of just 2.5 on TripAdvisor. And it showed. Even though we were put in a Junior Suite, it was a large, run-down hotel in an inferior location (see the reviews for yourself). Needless to say, we were less than pleased. Especially as we were only there for 3 nights! When I finally spoke to the manager (of the Radisson), she offered us a free meal. But never once did they offer to upgrade us. In fact, when we finally got into our room, we had to ask a couple of times for our champagne.To be fair though, after this rather unfortunate incident, the hotel was generally fine. Excellent location, friendly and helpful staff, with a nicely designed interior (although I still thought our room had a bit of a damp smell to it).Overall, I do think that our problem was probably a one-off. So I would still recommend this hotel. And the food was also very good. I just wish we'd realised that the drinks were free too...Finally, contrary to popular belief, we found the people in Paris to be very friendly. 
