<Author>FrequenttravelerSFCA
<Content>Great stay in Paris Just returned from a seven night stay at the Radisson Paris. It was my wife's first time to Paris, although I have been several times and have stayed in properties ranging from very small boutique hotels to the Meurice. Overall, the Radisson delivered on the Parisian experience. The location is fantastic, located in the 8th district just off the Champs Elysees. Very good restaurants, cafes, and shopping are very close by, and the George V metro stop is less than 5 mins walk. Next door is a sort of drugstore that also sells books, pastries, sundries and drinks (incl spirits) which is very convenient. Breakfast (we had the continental each morning) was very good. The service was excellent, both at the concierge and in the restaurant. The staff speaks excellent English and are very helpful, although for food recommendations, we would recommend a Zagat or Michelin guide for the true foodie in Paris. Rooms were clean, decorated with a modern flair, and roomy (~200 sq feet) for Parisian standards. Bed and linens were very comfortable. In room bar and safe provided. Our room had a limited view of the street, although we have been told Eiffel Tower views are available.The only complaints we would have would be the overall cleanliness of the bathrooms. The bathrooms themselves are of a good size - however, the sink is of a unique shape, and like previous reviewers have commented, difficult to keep clean. Likewise, we felt the shower could have been somewhat cleaner. Otherwise, an overall excellent stay, with a very friendly and helpful staff. Value for money is debatable (we paid 350 euros ~ 500 USD) but this just seems to be Europe nowadays. 
