<Author>elaine3766
<Content>Fabulous! We stayed here for six nights towards the end of April. The location is excellent. If you exit the hotel and turn right and then right again (and either pass through the Publicis drugstore or walk down the side of it), you're on the Champs Elysee - and right beside the Arc de Triomphe within a minute! A very impressive location.Unfortunately, the hotel seemed to be undergoing major upgrading works for the duration of our stay. Our room on the first floor was in the thick of it and it got worse and worse (a double bed lying in the corridor for two days and a very strong stench of something which smelled like superglue which eventually made its way into our room from the corridor). We paid a lot of money for our stay here (relatively speaking) and we were very disappointed to be living in a building site. We complained and the staff were very helpful and explained that they had to do the upgrading works now before the peak season (June). They explained that the management had taken the decision to keep the hotel open during the renovation works and that they were sorry for the inconvenience and would report our comments to the management. From what I could gather, other residents were affected too and some were turned away and relocated to another hotel because their room was not available! We were moved to another room on the seventh floor, which was much better as there was no refurb taking place.... until our second last day when five French men decided to remove the ceiling in the main corridor! We think they were installing air con in the landings on each floor, which makes sense as the remainder of the hotel has air con and the landings are very warm indeed.Aside from all of this (I guess it was just bad-timing on our/their part), the hotel is fabulous. The bedrooms are incredibly modern and they seem brand new, with plasma tv screens and white linen on the beds. I have no idea why the rooms need renovated, but perhaps they are meticulously up-dated each year to ensure that a high/modern standard is retained. The fittings are dark brown/steel/stone and lovely. The bathroom sink looks very funky, although it's a bit impractical as there is no sink plug and nor can you fill the sink! The shower and bath were great.The cleaning staff are excellent and the rooms are always spotless.... why does the toilet roll require a neat triangle at the end (during the morning clean AND the evening bed turn down)?! Breakfast was excellent, although not included in our deal. We were disappointed about this; we booked through Expedia and the implication was that breakfast was included. We know there were other guests staying at the hotel who were paying less than us and they had some sort of inclusive deal. Shop around before you book.The staff were excellent and courteous.The communal areas are beautiful and modern, with lovely cream suede chairs etc in the bar area. The bar prices are awful, though - far too expensive (about 14 euros for a gin and tonic!) and the mini bar is prohibitive (8.5 euros for a diet coke..... you can buy a diet coke for 1 euro in the Publicis drugstore - try that instead).I'd recommend this hotel to anyone. We'd stay there again. A fabulous location and very clean, luxurious and modern. A delight. Just don't visit in April when they're renovating... ! 
