<Content>Nice Hotel  We have just returned from 4 nights at the Radisson Champs Elysee. The hotel is well situated for many attractions and is within 1 block of the champs Elysee and the Arc de Triomphe. The hotel is very clean and modern and the staff there were so helpful and friendly, they could not do enough for you. We had a room on the 6th floor and had a view of the Arc de Trtiomphe  the Eiffel Tower from our balcony. The room was very nice, clean  modern,although a little on the small side, but worth it for the view we had. The hotel staff will be happy to arrange everything from tours to restaurant reservations for you. One tip, take time out to have a meal at the hotel as the food and service was excellent. The only draw back with the hotel  I am being very picky now, was that it was slightly noisy with the road outside, but some ear plugs sorted that little problem out and we slept very well. Good shop  restaurant on the corner and a good french cafe across the road that is popular with the locals. 
