<Content>Merci My wife and I vacationed in Paris Christmas week through New Year's Day. As this was our first trip to Paris we were a bit anxious about what to expect from our accommodations as well as the people. We've travelled in Europe and learned that four/five star U.S. and the same rating oversees don't always match up. Let me assure you that both the hotel and the people were fantastic. Even before arriving in Paris I worked with our concierge, Arnaud, to plan restaurant and tour reservations. I found Arnaud and his team to be very knowledgeable and flexible in meeting our needs. For example, my wife and I walked the city all day and came to our hotel at about 10 pm hungry and tired. The staff ordered us a pizza, set it up in the lounge with china and candelight and the meal cost us only $13 euros. The hotel was beautiful. It reminded me very much of the W Union Square in NYC. It's well designed, classy and a bit cutting-edge (club music is played in the lobby). Our room had high ceilings, a beautiful bay window, hardwood floors, contemporary furnishings and a large bathroom with a great shower and good water pressure. The people we met in the lobby lounge (both staff and other guests) were very friendly and helpful in giving us tips on where to go and what to do. Even minor inconveniences were handled well by the staff. On our last day the hotel had a serious plumbing issue which meant we had to shower in cold water. To make up for this inconvenience the staff simply reduced our rate for the day. When we return to Paris we'll return to the Radisson. Merci! 
